

Latin America's three major stock markets closed lower on Thursday.

Mexico City's IPC stock index dropped by 0.22 percent to close at 24,266.03 points. A total of 116 million shares were traded at 339 million U.S. dollars.

The Buenos Aires stock market closed with the Merval index down 1.38 percent at 1,891.51 points. The trade volume was 16.91 million dollars.

In Sao Paulo, Latin America's biggest bourse, the leading Bovespa index closed at 41,161 points, down 0.31 percent. The trade volume was 1.48 billion dollars.

